<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,258,940]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,242,258,283]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">MALE.</emphasis>
Body length not measureable, wing length 
<quantity box="[742,833,259,283]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[845,916,258,283]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Head.</emphasis>
Lost in the single specimen. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1254,1350,258,283]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Thorax.</emphasis>
Colour mainly brownish, faintly pollinose; postalar callus pale brown; the pile short, adpressed, pale; scutellum shiny, the pile similar to posterior part of scutum but darker brownish, the vestiture at apical margin damaged. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1275,1346,330,355]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Wing.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<figureCitation box="[180,246,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,248,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[225,1354,364,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[222,1365,358,1516]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Wing. A. Sphegina (Sphegina) uncinata sp. n. (paratype). B. S. (Asiosphegina) furva sp. n. (paratype). C. S. (A.) nasuta sp. n. (paratype). D. S. (A.) crucivena sp. n. (paratype). E. S. (A.) crassispina sp. n. (paratype). F. S. (A.) bidens sp. n. (paratype). G. S. (A.) carinata sp. n. (paratype). H. S. (A.) index sp. n. (paratype). I. S. (A.) simplex sp. n. (paratype). Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288398/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[231,246,367,391]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D, hyalinous, stigma pale, the darker pattern brownish; note the extra cross vein between vein R 
<number box="[1324,1332,381,395]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[1405,1413,381,395]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1422,1429,381,395]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,214,405,430]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Legs.</emphasis>
Pro- and mesoleg yellow, tarsomeres 
<number box="[684,698,406,430]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="4.0">4</number>
and 
<number box="[766,780,405,430]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="5.0">5</number>
brownish. Metaleg: coxa brownish; trochanter simple, brownish; femur yellow on the basal 
<number box="[586,596,442,466]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[607,623,442,466]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
, brownish on the apical 
<number box="[912,922,442,466]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[934,950,442,466]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
, with an indication of a darker submedial annulus; tibia without an apico-ventral tooth, brownish, the extreme base and an annulus on the apical 
<number box="[1400,1410,478,502]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1421,1437,478,502]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
yellowish; tarsus brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[436,560,513,538]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergites I and II in dorsal view similar to 
<figureCitation box="[1046,1112,513,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[177,1357,207,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[174,1384,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Tergite I (A – E), lateral view, abdomen (F, G, H), dorsal view. A, F. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) simplex sp. n. (paratype). B. S. (A.) gigas sp. n. (paratype). C. S. (A.) radula sp. n. (paratype). D, H. S. (A.) crassispina sp. n. (paratype). E, G. S. (A.) parvula sp. n. (paratype). Scale 0.5 mm for A – E, 1 mm for F, G, H." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288400/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[1098,1112,514,538]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F, the more apical segments, except for genitalia, lost; the colour of tergites shiny brown, the pile short, adpressed and brownish, becoming longer and pale towards the lateral margin; tergite I with 
<number box="[815,829,586,610]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
rather close together placed strong, pale setae at the lateral margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[321,438,621,646]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Genitalia,</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[445,529,621,646]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1944,1966]" captionTargetBox="[260,1330,1004,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[247,1339,995,1922]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 20. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) mirifica sp. n. (holotype). A. Aedeagus, lateral view. B. Genitalia, lateral view. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288416/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Figs 
<number box="[500,529,622,646]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
A–C. Symmetrical. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[752,879,621,646]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">FEMALE.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
