<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,258,940]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,693,718]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is Latin, 
<taxonomicName box="[560,649,693,717]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirifica">
<emphasis box="[560,649,693,717]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">mirifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, causing wonder, referring to the extraordinary cross vein between R 
<number box="[1428,1436,708,722]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[217,225,747,761]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[234,241,747,761]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,258,940]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,771,796]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[346,553,771,795]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirifica">
<emphasis box="[346,553,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Sphegina mirifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[728,860,771,795]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forficata">
<emphasis box="[728,860,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">S. forficata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[928,1073,771,795]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucivena">
<emphasis box="[928,1073,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">S. crucivena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition to the characters mentioned in the key it differs by the following characters in the male genitalia: 
<number box="[1103,1115,807,831]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1.0">1</number>
) surstylus is more strongly curved and broad (not attenuated) at the apex, 
<number box="[706,721,843,867]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="2.0">2</number>
) aedeagal lobe is angulate (not smoothly curved) and 
<number box="[1367,1381,843,867]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
) the ejaculatory hood is very short (long). The superior lobe is large and long as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1089,1231,879,903]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucivena">
<emphasis box="[1089,1231,879,903]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">S. crucivena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but straight (not angularly curved).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
